    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Sedentary, fishing-based society based in southern Florida, particularly around Key Marco. Flourished from ca. 1000 CE to the mid 1700s; European diseases and conflict led to the Calusa's collapse. Known for large temple mounds, canals, and shell carving. </Note_Text>
